BM__Toc30479244BM__Toc29274013

Receipt Dates. Grant applications submitted in response to this SBIR/STTR
Omnibus Grant Solicitation will be considered "on time" if received by or
mailed on or before the published receipt date and a proof of mailing is
provided. Proof of timely mailing consists of one of the following: a
legibly dated U.S. Postal Service postmark or a dated receipt from a
commercial carrier or the U.S. Postal Service. Private metered postmarks are
not acceptable.



Remember to check the NIH Guide for Grants and Contracts

http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/index.html periodically for Special

Announcements that apply to the Small Business Research Community.  These

Program Announcements (PAs) and Requests for Applications (RFAs) are ways
the

Institutes "emphasize" areas of high priority.  This is a great way to keep
abreast of where the Institutes/Centers are focusing their immediate
interests.



Conferences. Lastly, there are a number of SBIR/STTR Conferences on the
