<h2><a name="_Toc30479242"></a><a name="_Toc30219897"></a><a name="_Toc30218302"></a><a
name="_Toc30218553"></a><a name="_Toc29274011"><b><font size=4 face=Arial><span
style='font-size:14.0pt'>REMINDERS</span></font></b></a></h2>

</div>

<p class=MsoPlainText><a name="_Toc30479243"></a><a name="_Toc29274012"><b><font
size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold'>Forms</span></font></b></a><b><span
style='font-weight:bold'>. </span></b>All SBIR and STTR applications (Phase I,
Phase II, and Phase I/Phase II Fast-Track) must be submitted using the Public
Health Service Grant Application <a
href="http://grants.nih.gov/grants/funding/phs398/phs398.html"><font
color=black><span style='color:windowtext;text-decoration:none'>(</span></font>PHS
398<font color=black><span style='color:windowtext;text-decoration:none'>)</span></font></a>
in accordance with the <span class=MsoHyperlink><u><font color=blue>Specific
SBIR/STTR Grant Application Instructions and Requirements</font></u></span><em><i><u>
described in this Solicitation and the PHS 398 instructions</u></i></em>.</p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><a name="_Toc30479244"></a><a name="_Toc29274013"><b><font
size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold'>&nbsp;</span></font></b></a></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><b><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-weight:bold'>Receipt Dates</span></font></b><b><span style='font-weight:
bold'>. </span></b>Grant applications submitted <em><i><u>in response to this
SBIR/STTR Omnibus Grant Solicitation</u></i></em> will be considered <em><i><u>"on
time" if received by or mailed on or before the published receipt date
and a proof of mailing is provided</u></i></em>. Proof of timely mailing
consists of one of the following: a legibly dated U.S. Postal Service postmark
or a dated receipt from a commercial carrier or the U.S. Postal Service.
Private metered postmarks are not acceptable. </p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Remember
to check the NIH Guide for Grants and Contracts</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/index.html
periodically for Special</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Announcements
that apply to the Small Business Research Community.&nbsp; These</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Program
Announcements (PAs) and Requests for Applications (RFAs) are ways the</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Institutes
&quot;emphasize&quot; areas of high priority.&nbsp; This is a great way to keep
abreast of where the Institutes/Centers are focusing their immediate interests.</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>&nbsp;</span></font></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><b><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-weight:bold'>Conferences.</span></font></b> Lastly, there are a number of
SBIR/STTR Conferences on the horizon. </p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>The
next National Conference is&nbsp; </span></font>March 11-14, 2003 in Albuquerque, NM.</p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>The
5<sup>th</sup> (!!) Annual NIH SBIR/STTR Conference will be held </span></font>June 2-3, 2003 in Bethesda, MD </p>

